OL,3,C'There are others like us': Government
OL,4,Cconsidering changing Mental Capacity
OL,5,CAct
OL,7,F'I believed he would die'
OL,9,FOne mother told ITV News that her
OL,10,Fautistic son has been sectioned after
OL,11,Fdeteriorating for years because the
OL,12,Fauthorities judged that he had
OL,13,Fcapacity to decide that he didn't need
OL,14,Fany support.
OL,16,FParveen's son would spend day and
OL,17,Fnight in bed not eating or drinking
OL,18,Fand fought for years to try to get him
OL,19,Fa mental capacity assessment in the
OL,20,Fhopes that it would get him the help
OL,21,Fhe desperately needed.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
